{
  "doc_id": "57011",
  "text": "The lattice Boltzmann method has been proposed as a discretization of Boltzmann's kinetic equation and is now in wide use in fluid dynamics and beyond (for an introduction and review see [CITATION_1] ). Instead of fields of moments M, the lattice Boltzmann method operates with fields of discrete distributions f . This allows us to construct very simple limiters that do not depend on slopes or gradients.",
